    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 18 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-14618 AND RTLO-16618
        SERIES - DISASSEMBLE - FRONT AUXILIARY DRIVE GEAR
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="7">
        <title>FRONT AUXILIARY DRIVE GEAR</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f13019d8">Figure 138</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f13019d8" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13019d8" filename="../figg13/G13019d8.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 138. Front Auxiliary Drive Gear Exploded View</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Cut the lockwire from the auxiliary bearing retainer ring bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13019d9">Figure 139</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13019d9" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13019d9" filename="../figg13/G13019d9.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 139. Cut Lockwire From Auxiliary Bearing Retainer Ring Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the snap ring from the mainshaft rear groove (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13019e0">Figure 140</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13019e0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13019e0" filename="../figg13/G13019e0.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 140. Remove Snap Ring From Mainshaft Rear Groove</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the splined washer from inside the front auxiliary drive gear assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13019e1">Figure 141</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13019e1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13019e1" filename="../figg13/G13019e1.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 141. Remove Splined Washer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the six bolts from the auxiliary bearing retainer ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13019e2">Figure 142</hotlnk>). Insert three puller bolts in the specially tapped holes
                of the retainer ring. Tighten the bolts evenly to pull the front auxiliary drive gear assembly from the
                case bore.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13019e2" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13019e2" filename="../figg13/G13019e2.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 142. Remove Bolts From Auxiliary Bearing Retainer Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the front auxiliary drive gear from the aft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13019e3">Figure 143</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13019e3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13019e3" filename="../figg13/G13019e3.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 143. Remove Front Auxiliary Drive Gear From Mainshaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the splined washer from the mainshaft. Also remove the front auxiliary drive gear
                retaining snap ring from the mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13019e4">Figure 144</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13019e4" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13019e4" filename="../figg13/G13019e4.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 144. Remove Splined Washer From Mainshaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
